### Test Dashboard and New Features

### 1. Create a task WITHOUT a worker (new feature!)
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Unassigned Task",
  "description": "This task has no worker assigned",
  "dueDate": "2024-12-31",
  "status": {"statusId": 1},
  "category": {"categoryId": 1}
}

###

### 2. Create a task WITH a worker
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Assigned Task",
  "description": "This task has a worker",
  "dueDate": "2024-12-31",
  "workerId": 1,
  "status": {"statusId": 1},
  "category": {"categoryId": 1}
}

###

### 3. Create another task with same worker
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Second Assigned Task",
  "description": "Another task for same worker",
  "dueDate": "2024-12-31",
  "workerId": 1,
  "status": {"statusId": 2},
  "category": {"categoryId": 2}
}

###

### 4. Get all tasks (check worker_id values)
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks

###

### 5. Delete a worker (should unassign from tasks via gRPC!)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/workers/1

###

### 6. Get all tasks again (worker_id should now be null for previously assigned tasks)
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks

###

### 7. Get Dashboard (NEW ENDPOINT!)
GET http://localhost:8080/dashboard

###

### 8. Get Dashboard History (NEW ENDPOINT!)
GET http://localhost:8080/dashboard/history

###

### 9. Update a task
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "taskName": "Updated Task Name",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "dueDate": "2025-01-15",
  "status": {"statusId": 2},
  "category": {"categoryId": 1}
}

###

### 10. Create a new worker
POST http://localhost:8080/workers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workerName": "Jane",
  "workerLastName": "Smith"
}

###

### 11. View updated dashboard
GET http://localhost:8080/dashboard

###

### 12. View history (should show all operations)
GET http://localhost:8080/dashboard/history

###

### Test Scenarios

# Scenario 1: Task without worker lifecycle
# 1. Create task without worker (request #1)
# 2. View dashboard - should show 1 task
# 3. View history - should show CREATE action

# Scenario 2: Worker deletion unassigns tasks
# 1. Create worker
# 2. Create 2 tasks assigned to that worker
# 3. Delete worker (request #5)
# 4. Get all tasks (request #6) - both tasks should have worker_id = null
# 5. View history - should show worker deletion

# Scenario 3: Dashboard tracking
# 1. Perform various operations (create/update/delete tasks and workers)
# 2. Check dashboard (request #7) - should show:
#    - Correct count of workers
#    - Correct count of tasks
#    - Tasks grouped by status
#    - Tasks grouped by category
# 3. Check history (request #8) - should show recent 20 operations
